<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Ambassador in China (
                        Stuart
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d967</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">967</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-07-30T09:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-07-30T09:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-30T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-30T09:00:00-05:00" n="967" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d967">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Stuart, J. Leighton: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-30T22:00:00+08:00">July 30, 1949—10 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 30—11:20 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1664. With reference Deptel 875, July 23,<note n="45" xml:id="d967fn45">Not
                        printed.</note> I am making every effort to depart not later than morning
                    August 2. (See Embtel 1663, July 30.) Communist authorities declare they require
                    time properly to alert their armed forces along aircraft’s course and that
                    August 2 is only tentative ETD. They said I will not be delayed longer than
                    August 3 in any event.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
